column5: My can is a plastic Folgers
Looks like easy boat launching.Here eagle dock at VB.water level even with dock.
Later in the day, docks back in place. In the first picture the part of the dock that is under water is normally a couple of feet above the water.
wow looks like marcel has some work to do
As of yesterday Eagle Lake water levels were at 1191 feet above sea level...the highest it's been since 1947. The top of the dam in Eagle River is 1192.

Water levels on Rainy are approaching the 2014 flood levels. Docks all have barrels to keep them from floating away. Sandbagging operations are under way. They expect the level to rise another 13" if we don't get anymore rain. They put no wake restrictions of 300 feet from the shoreline on yesterday. Gord did you get the big rains Wednesday night into Thursday?
We did get rain overnight but not what they were predicting. Not sure if it missed us or where it went. The radar looked nasty before I went to bed. It's been a crazy spring.
I'm sure he uses the lake as a range gauge.
I use a coffee can on my deck as a rain gauge
Maybe Prov1800 has a coffee can you can use 🤣
Put some grounds in the can,put alittle fire under it,wait for the rain wala you got some joe.
